alert.note: Alert for Coastal Bay; Coastal Franklin; Coastal Gulf (Florida) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 09 at 9:59AM EST until January 09 at 1:00PM EST by NWS Tallahassee
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 1 PM EST /NOON CST/ THIS AFTERNOON... ...WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 1 PM EST /NOON CST/ THIS AFTERNOON TO MIDNIGHT EST /11 PM CST/ TONIGHT... * WHAT...For the High Wind Warning, southwest winds 30 to 40 mph with gusts up to 60 mph. For the Wind Advisory, west winds 25 to 35 mph with gusts up to 50 mph expected. * WHERE...Coastal Bay, Coastal Gulf and Coastal Franklin Counties. * WHEN...For the High Wind Warning, until 1 PM EST /noon CST/ this afternoon. For the Wind Advisory, from 1 PM EST /noon CST/ this afternoon to midnight EST /11 PM CST/ tonight. * IMPACTS...Damaging winds will blow down trees and power lines. Widespread power outages are expected. Travel will be difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.
info.instruction: People should avoid being outside in forested areas and around trees and branches. If possible, remain in the lower levels of your home during the windstorm, and avoid windows. Use caution if you must drive.
